contracts.description:
Since I released my first EP in 2016 I’ve realized that making full length projects is a really important fuel to my creativity. Also the feeling of freedom and a fresh start I get after putting out a project I have worked on for a long time. It allows a period of mindless producing that eventually finds a direction and purpose that often and hopefully results in a project that’s very different from the previous. 

As I’ve gotten older (now 26) I’ve become more aware of how I get drawn to certain palettes over periods of time and how I can use this to make more cohesive projects. Thinking more conceptual with my sound choices and moods gives me a bigger feeling of purpose when making music. 

“Got It” is a result of the last couple years where I’ve been drawn towards medieval sounding things. Harpsichords, worn instruments, simple, folky (no pun) sounding music. It’s the first single from my upcoming project “Castle Tapes” and it captures a lot of the palette that has been inspiring me the last couple years. Hope you enjoy it! Cheers!

Wet In Desires is a nude photography project I discovered the human body once again in a creative way. I sought the essence of sexual desire in human body and gestures during the creative process.  
Our sexual attention can easily triggered by physical appearance. Also gestures may be really attracting for us too. I focused on these 2 visual aspect and benefited by long exposure, double exposure on camera techniques to create a ''desire moment'' effect in photograph. 'Colored Water' and 'Light' represent the space conquered by desires.

There is an EGGsly™ in each of us. 

EGGsly is a gender-neutral collection of 2422 randomly generated NFTs built from 330 unique hand-drawn traits and exists on the Ethereum Blockchain. Each EGGsly NFT acts as a mint pass to participate in the upcoming claim(s). 

There is also an OG collection, the first 75 created in 2021 on the polygon blockchain. Each OG NFT is hand-assembled, and some are animated in Photoshop, making them one-of-a-kind, and were dropped starting September 3, 2021. 

Created and illustrated by Karrie Ross. She shares her love of EGGs, and the actions of observation and play are exampled in each piece of art. NFTs #1-10 of the OG collection are the building parts of EGGsly, the remaining are emotions and adventures.

Connecting artists with their art through their masks is the objective of this collection. 

No better way to start than with Vincent Van Gogh. Starry night (1889) was inspired with Van Gogh's stay in an asylum in Saint-Rémy. 

Is life without art worth living? Sanity, connection and community is just some of the things it brings.
